{
  "doc_id": "57344",
  "text": "A novel Baylisascaris species,B. potosis, was recently described in kinkajous (Potos flavus). Type specimens were collected from captive kinkajous that originated in Cooperative Republic of Guyana [CITATION_1] . This species is morphologically similar to B. procyonis but was described as a new species based on genetic analysis of several gene targets (i.e., internal transcribed spacer (ITS) 2 region, 28S rRNA gene, and COX1 gene) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Kinkajous are common exotic pets in the United States and other countries.",
